{
  "text": "iii In particular, we use data on the sub-sample of domestically owned firms, distinguishing between the three categories of firms mentioned above (i.e. domestic market, exporters, outward FDI). We further split our sample of domesticallyowned firms into manufacturing and services firms to examine whether the productivity ordering differs between manufacturing and services firms, as hypothesised by [CITATION_1] . This is the first paper that we are aware of that examines this productivity ordering for SSA firms,",
